{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Backend-Driven (Recommended)\n      How it works: The existing call transcript WebSocket streams text to the backend. A new LocationExtractor service runs on each transcript chunk — regex for addresses/streets, city name dictionary lookup, and area code mapping. When a location is found, a location_detected event is pushed over the same WebSocket with coordinates.\n      Geocoding: Nominatim (free, OpenStreetMap-based) or a local city/zip lookup table for common mentions like \"Spring Hill\", \"Franklin\", \"Mt. Pleasant\".\n      \n        Pros\n          \n            Transcript + location parsing in one place\n            Can match against CRM customer DB server-side\n            No extra API keys or client-side processing\n            Drive time calculation on server (haversine already exists)\n          \n        \n        Cons\n          \n            Slight latency (~200-500ms) for geocoding round-trip\n            More backend code to maintain","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1775493314617}
